        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 26 at 12:21PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 1220 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Faysville, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Memorial Middle School, Cesar Chavez, Economedes High School, Red
Gate, Hargill, Jose Borrego Middle School, Eisenhower Elementary
School, Monte Cristo Elementary School, San Manuel, and Hargill
Reservoir.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate Highway 69 C between mile markers 9 and 12.
US Highway 281 between mile markers 748 and 764.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
